Great ‚Äî this screenshot is the last missing piece.
Your isSubmitDisabled() logic is basically correct, but it still references shared state that caused all the problems.

I‚Äôll show you exactly what to change and what NOT to touch, so you don‚Äôt regress anything.

‚∏ª

üî¥ The real problem in isSubmitDisabled()

You currently use:

this.isFormValid
this.currentFormValues
this.complaintDialogSubmitted

But now you have two different forms:

Context	Should use
Main screen (Complete / Pend / Return etc.)	isFormValid, currentFormValues
Cancel ‚Üí Complaint dialog	isComplaintFormValid, complaintFormValues

The good news:
Your Cancel logic already correctly uses complaintDialogSubmitted.
We only need to make one small but critical clarification.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ EXACT FIX for isSubmitDisabled()

üîß Change ONLY this block (Cancel case)

‚ùå Current code

if (saveRequestObject.action === SwftStageActions.CANCEL_REQUEST && this.requestDetails?.complaintCaptured) {
  const reason = workflowForm?.stageActionReasonField;

  // Enable only if complaintDialogSubmitted is true
  status = !!reason && this.complaintDialogSubmitted;
}

‚úÖ Keep it EXACTLY the same

This part is already correct üëç
DO NOT add isFormValid here ‚Äî Cancel does NOT depend on main form validity.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ REQUIRED CHANGE for Complete action (THIS IS THE FIX)

‚ùå Current code

else if (saveRequestObject.action && saveRequestObject.action === SwftWorkflowActions.CompleteAction) {
  if (this.approvalCompleted && this.isFormValid && saveRequestObject.statusName) {
    status = true;
    if (!this.validateDynamicFormRequiredFields()) {
      status = false;
    }
  }
}

‚úÖ Replace with this

else if (saveRequestObject.action === SwftWorkflowActions.CompleteAction) {
  if (
    this.approvalCompleted &&
    this.isFormValid &&                 // ‚úÖ MAIN form validity only
    saveRequestObject.statusName
  ) {
    status = this.validateDynamicFormRequiredFields();
  }
}

üìå This does two important things:
	1.	Guarantees Complete NEVER depends on dialog validity
	2.	Prevents dialog eForm from enabling Complete accidentally

‚∏ª

‚úÖ ONE MORE REQUIRED FIX (small but important)

When action switches away from Cancel, you MUST reset complaint state
(otherwise old Cancel dialog submissions leak into Complete).

Add this where action changes

Wherever you set:

saveRequestObject.action = ...

Add:

if (saveRequestObject.action !== SwftStageActions.CANCEL_REQUEST) {
  this.complaintDialogSubmitted = false;
  this.isComplaintFormValid = false;
  this.complaintFormValues = null;
}

This is critical.

